      {"name": "Elijah (translated)", "role": "Taken up to heaven in a whirlwind at the opening of the book (ch. 2); his translation without death, and the expectation of his return (Mal 4:5), makes him a unique eschatological figure"},
      {"name": "Jehu", "role": "Anointed to destroy Ahab's house; his zeal for YHWH is genuine but ruthless, illustrating that reform without a changed heart produces limited and temporary results"}
